  <XDFTABLE uniqueid="0x229" flags="0x30">
    <title>Likely Spark Advance Low Octane / Alternate 24x9 @ 0x8B41</title>
    <description>Single retained view for the alternate code-confirmed spark bank at 0x8B41. The routine at 0x48EE loads X with 0x8B41 when spark_bank_selector_state RAM 0x20B1 is zero, builds a B2D6 descriptor at 0x213A with axis 1 from RAM 0x2034 and axis 2 from RAM 0x2036, sets column count to 9, and accumulates the result into the spark-angle command path around RAM 0x2147. Byte 0x8C18 is row 23 column 8 of this bank. Values display plausibly as spark advance with X/2 degree scaling. Compared with 0x8A69, this bank is not simply lower everywhere: it has more advance in some mid-load cells, but is usually lower in high-load columns, supporting the likely low-octane/alternate label. X labels are provisional MAP/load values derived from the 0x2034 8.8 axis range and 100 kPa PRT03-family MAP sensor evidence; exact ECU transfer/scaling is still not proven.</description>
