  <XDFTABLE uniqueid="0x22C" flags="0x30">
    <title>Likely WOT Spark Advance Vector 1x24 @ 0x8C19</title>
    <description>Code at 0x48F4 bypasses the 0x8A69/0x8B41 banked 2D maps when RAM 0x00A9 bit 0x20 is set and instead calls the 1D interpolation helper at 0xB2AB with Y=0x8C19 and D=RAM 0x2036. Because 0x2036 is the RPM axis and the bytes display as plausible spark values with raw / 2 degree scaling, this is a likely wide-open-throttle or fallback spark advance vector. MOD2 does not change this vector.</description>
