  <XDFTABLE uniqueid="0x22D" flags="0x30">
    <title>Load Model / Correction Factor Candidate 24x9 @ 0x9187</title>
    <description>Medium-high structural confidence view for the code-confirmed 0x9187 24x9 lookup. The routine at 0x6344 builds a B2D6 descriptor at RAM 0x218D, derives one axis through helper 0xB383 using vector 0x9291 and count/stride byte 0x929A=9, loads the second axis from RPM-like RAM 0x2036, sets base 0x9187, and returns the interpolated byte. Known callers store the result at RAM 0x210F and RAM 0x00D0; one path then stores 0x00CE = 0x00D0 left-shifted by 2, feeding the 0x2034 load/MAP-like axis used by the spark maps. Values display with X / 230. Likely load-model, air, fuel, or correction factor; not proven main fuel.</description>
