  <XDFTABLE uniqueid="0x238" flags="0x30">
    <title>Likely Fuel/VE/Air-Charge Correction Candidate 21x9 @ 0x802E</title>
    <description>Primary working view for the likely fuel/VE/air-charge correction surface at 0x802E. It uses the public-index 21x9 alignment with RPM-like rows 550-6000 and load/MAP-like columns 0-1024. Peugeot stock raw values are 135-248, about 52.9-97.3 percent if viewed as raw / 2.55; Xantia 607C at the same offset is 144-214, about 56.5-83.9 percent. MOD2 raises selected Peugeot cells mostly by +4 to +6 raw counts. This is clearly not spark and is the strongest current fuel-side candidate, but raw / 2.55 is only a visualization hypothesis and no code consumer into injection pulse width, fuel time, lambda correction, or air-charge calculation has been confirmed. Keep raw display and do not treat as confirmed main fuel.</description>
    <CATEGORYMEM index="0" category="5" />
